<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="439" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,899,1464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1044,1068]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[450,559,1044,1068]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Koppe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[450,468,1045,1068]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">K</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[482,559,1045,1068]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are closely related to the females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Deeleman-Reinhold, 2001" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[959,1347,1044,1068]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Koppe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baerti">
<emphasis box="[959,1055,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">K. baerti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." box="[1062,1347,1044,1068]" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" refId="ref2503" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L. (2001) Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic]). Brill, Leiden, 591 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004475588" type="book" year="2001">Deeleman-Reinhold, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as both share similar M-shaped anterior epigynal margin and vulva with highly twisted ducts, but can be distinguished from the latter by femur I with two prolateral spines (vs. absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[754,848,1116,1140]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Koppe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baerti">
<emphasis box="[754,772,1117,1140]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">K</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[784,848,1116,1140]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">baerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and epigynal window with triangular, median flap (vs. median flap absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[387,482,1152,1176]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Koppe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baerti">
<emphasis box="[387,405,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">K</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[418,482,1152,1176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">baerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[540,622,1152,1176]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." box="[673,952,1152,1176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" refId="ref2503" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L. (2001) Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic]). Brill, Leiden, 591 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004475588" type="book" year="2001">Deeleman-Reinhold 2001</bibRefCitation>
: figs 399–400).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,899,1464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,514,1187,1212]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439" reason="1">Supplementary description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[519,599,1188,1212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[613,728,1188,1212]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3A–G</figureCitation>
) in alcohol. Prosoma, chelicerae, palps and legs brownish; thoracic part with pale black patches; opisthosoma greyish-black, with brown dorsal scutum; spinnerets creamy-white. Fovea narrow, straight, short, dark (
<figureCitation box="[457,541,1260,1284]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). AER slightly and PER moderately procurved, both in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1264,1349,1260,1284]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Femur I with two prolateral spines, ventrally with numerous tiny, thorn-like spines (
<figureCitation box="[985,1101,1296,1320]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3D–E</figureCitation>
, arrows); tibia I with nine pro- and nine retrolateral ventral spines (
<figureCitation box="[533,647,1332,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3F–G</figureCitation>
); metatarsus I with six pro- and six retrolateral ventral spines (
<figureCitation box="[1310,1425,1332,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3F–G</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma globular, with complete dorsal scutum (
<figureCitation box="[731,817,1368,1392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@4.[209,1378,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Koppe armata (Simon, 1896), female from Sri Lanka. A prosoma, dorsal view; B same, prolateral view; C opisthosoma, prolateral view; D left femur I showing two prolateral spines, ventral view; E left femur I showing ventral thornlike spines, retrolateral view; F left tibia and metatarsus I showing prolateral ventral spines, prolateral view; G same, showing retrolateral ventral spines, retrolateral view; H epigyne, ventral view; I labels from the vial. Arrows indicate prolateral spines. Figures not to scales. © RMNH, Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332107/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="439">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
